The paper discusses the use of auto-encoders, a popular neural network architecture for dimension reduction, and proposes a new methodology called PHom-WAE that uses persistent homology to assess and measure the data distribution of a generative model. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of visualization techniques, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the comparison of different types of generative models, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
